<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nigeria Calls Up Retired Oil Workers: The nation's official radio said Labor 
Minister Samuel Ogbemudia had directed former oil officials to register for 
work with a view to being offered jobs. The military government is fighting a 
six-week strike by oil workers who support Moshood Abiola as president. Union 
leaders have vowed to continue the strike, which has disrupted fuel deliveries 
and cut oil output by about 20%. 
</P>
