<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Texaco, Norwegian Firm to Join Forces: Norway's Norsk Hydro and Texaco Inc. 
said they have signed a letter of intent to create a joint venture company to 
sell petroleum products in Norway and Denmark.Each partner would hold a 50% 
share in the new company, which encompasses only marketing activities. The new 
firm would also have a major presence in the diesel and heating fuel markets. 
"It combines Hydro's strong Scandinavian presence with Texaco's international 
experience and marketing expertise," the two companies said. 
</P>
