<HEADLINE>
<P>
'SOUND OF MUSIC' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "The Sound of Music" is "a problem" to be solved? (" 'Sound' Is Back With All 
Its Trappings," Aug. 11). The lyrics to "Oh, What a Beautiful Morning" are a 
"tired cliche"? And "My Favorite Things" contains a "lyric to choke on"? Then 
why give valuable space to something so un-hip as a musical? After all, songs 
and albums such as "Doggystyle," "Sexy MF," "Baby's Got Back," "Achy Breaky 
Heart" and "Smells Like Teen Spirit" could use some more exposure, and they are 
certain to stand the test of time a lot better than a tired old cliche like 
"The Sound of Music." 
</P>
<P>
 BRUCE BABCOCK 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 
</P>
