<HEADLINE>
<P>
'FORREST GUMP' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a world of instant gratification where one is increasingly viewed as real 
only as part of society and valued only insofar as one serves it, "Forrest 
Gump" succeeds when it reaffirms our deepest-held belief that individuals count 
and a proper (enlightened) life is possible. However, "Forrest Gump" fails when 
it portrays a man "overcoming" life's trials and tribulations -- not by 
applying his mind so much, as by being lucky. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES P. KOYHollywood 
