<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACID BARREL PUNCTURED; 23 WORKERS SLIGHTLY INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A forklift operator punctured a barrel of acid, creating fumes that caused 
minor injuries to 23 warehouse workers and three firefighters. About 11 gallons 
of cresylic acid spilled from the 15-gallon drum on Thursday. The odorless 
acid, used in plastics and disinfectants, is fatal if inhaled in large doses, 
officials said. 
</P>
