<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOODSTOCK '94 STRAGGLER IS ARRESTED AT THE SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nearly three days after the music stopped at Woodstock '94, a woman was 
arrested for refusing to leave the concert site. 
</P>
<P>
 Kathy Bowen, 32, of Bristol, Pa., became belligerent after being asked to 
leave the concert grounds Wednesday afternoon, state police said. The concert 
ended early Monday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 She was charged with criminal trespass and resisting arrest, and spent a night 
in the Ulster County Jail before being released Thursday, police said. 
</P>
