<HEADLINE>
<P>
GONZALES WINS DECISION OVER DE LA HOYA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding "His Torch Burns Out" (Aug 10): 
</P>
<P>
 After the 1992 Olympics, I twice wrote to Oscar De La Hoya, inviting him to be 
a guest speaker in my introductory course to Chicano Studies, but I did not get 
the courtesy of a response. 
</P>
<P>
 After the '84 Olympics, I wrote Paul Gonzales and his response was, "Yes, I 
would love to be a speaker." 
</P>
<P>
 That De La Hoya has been jeered during introductions to his recent boxing 
matches should surprise only outsiders. In character and style, Gonzales 
outranks De La Hoya. 
</P>
<P>
 JOSEPH PLATT 
</P>
<P>
 Professor of Chicano Studies 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 
</P>
