<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; FRESHMAN WASHINGTON GRABS SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With USC tailbacks Shawn Walters, David Dotson, Leonard Green and Rodney 
Sermons temporarily sidelined because of injuries, freshman Delon Washington 
seized the opportunity to shine in Friday afternoon's practice. 
</P>
<P>
 LaVale Woods, a freshman redshirt last season because of a knee injury, also 
played well. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington had several nice runs against the Trojans' first defense. A 10.33 
sprinter, Washington rushed for 1,579 yards, averaging 6.9 yards per carry, as 
a Dallas prep player last year. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Early last summer, USC journalism student/football player Tony Gnau landed a 
summer internship with Chicago television station WBBM. 
</P>
<P>
 As expected, he spent most of the time in the station's newsroom, learning 
about the daily gathering of TV news. But the station became shorthanded in 
late-summer and sports reporter Gnau was suddenly dispatched to ballparks and 
training camps for interviews. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was great, all of a sudden I was interviewing people on camera every day 
like Ryne Sandberg, Mark Grace and Rick Wilkins of the Cubs; Tim Raines, Alex 
Fernandez and Gene Lamont of the White Sox, and Mark Carrier and Curtis Conway 
of the Bears. 
</P>
<P>
 "I even interviewed Tommy Lasorda." 
</P>
<P>
 Gnau, a scout team senior, says he wants to work for a Chicago or Los Angeles 
television station after graduating.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Injuries: Shawn Walters' suffered a contusion after being hit in the back 
during run drills during Thursday's practice. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting center Robert Loya's foot injury is listed as a sprain and there has 
been significant healing, said trainer Jack Ward. "He'll be out days, not 
weeks," Ward said. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
