<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NATION; FLORIDA NO. 1; USC 14TH, 
UCLA 15TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Florida made school history by becoming the first Gator team to be ranked No. 
1 in the USA TODAY/CNN poll. USC and UCLA held down the 14th and 15th spots 
respectively. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gators apparently welcome the poll, which gave them a slight edge over 
last season's No. 1 team, Florida State, with 17 first-place votes to the 
Seminoles' 13. Florida had 1,416 total points to Florida State's 1,402. The 
teams will meet on Nov. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's what you come to college for," Gator defensive back Larry Kennedy 
said. "To be No. 1. That's what we all dream about." 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Steve Spurrier likes his team's chances, saying, "I don't know if we can 
hold it, but I would think our team is about as good as anyone around." 
</P>
<P>
 Nebraska (1,375) was No. 3 while Notre Dame (1,362) and Michigan (1,302) were 
fourth and fifth. The Irish and Wolverines play on Sept. 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona (1,037) was the highest ranked Pac-10 school at No. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 USC had 692 points and UCLA had 677. 
</P>
</TEXT>
