<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROLLER HOCKEY; BLADES AND BULLFROGS ADVANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Blades beat the San Diego Barracudas, 9-8, after an overtime shootout to 
advance to the Pacific Division finals in a Roller Hockey International playoff 
game at the Forum on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Barracudas tied the score, 8-8, with 39 seconds remaining to force a 
five-on-five shootout, which the Blades won, 2-1, on goals by Nick Vachon and 
Mike Callahan.Blade goaltender Max Mikhailovsky stopped four shots in the 
shootout. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blades, who swept the two games from San Diego, will play the Bullfrogs 
Tuesday in Anaheim. The two teams will play again on Wednesday in the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Bullfrogs 7, San Jose 6 -- Victor Gervais had two goals and two assists for 
the Bullfrogs in front of 8,130 at The Pond of Anaheim as the Bullfrogs won the 
series, two games to none. 
</P>
<P>
 Goalie Rob Laurie had 41 saves, Kevin Kerr had a goal and two assists and 
Steve Beadle had three assists for Anaheim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
