<P>
BOY, 15, FACING ADULT TRIAL IN SLAYING OF GRANDMOTHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old boy who shot his grandmother to death is likely to be tried as 
an adult and subject to the death penalty, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 A police spokesman said the suspect, whose identity was not made public, shot 
Laura Cholewa, 54, in the face with her own gun after she caught him 
burglarizing her house on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The youth was being held on charges of murder, burglary and theft of a 
firearm. 
