<HEADLINE>
<P>
LONGTIME ST. BONIFACE PASTOR QUATANNENS DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rev. Monsignor John Quatannens, longtime pastor of St. Boniface Church in 
Anaheim, died Friday. He was 85. 
</P>
<P>
 Born in Belgium in 1909, Quatannens was graduated from the American College of 
Louvain University in Belgium and ordained as a priest on Dec. 21, 1936.He 
arrived in Southern California in 1937. 
</P>
<P>
 As a young priest, Quatannens served as an assistant pastor in the Archdiocese 
of Los Angeles. He later served as a chaplain in the U.S. Army, under the 
command of Gen. George Patton, during the Battle of the Bulge, and in the Air 
Force during the Korean War. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1958, he was appointed pastor at St. Boniface, and he served there until 
his retirement in 1971. He was named monsignor in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
 Funeral liturgy will be said at 7 p.m. Tuesday at St. Boniface, 120 N. Janss 
St., Anaheim, with a rite of committal Wednesday at 10 a.m. in the Holy 
Sepulcher Cemetery in Orange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
