<TEXT>
<P>
 International Sports 
</P>
<P>
 Fabrice Colas and Frederic Magne of France captured the last world title of a 
disappearing specialty -- tandem -- while Ingrid Haringa of the Netherlands, a 
Dutch policewoman, set a record streak of four golds in a race with an Olympic 
future -- women's points -- at the world cycling championships in Palermo, 
Italy. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 John Andretti barely lost the pole to Geoff Bodine in the opening round of 
qualifying for Sunday's GM Goodwrench Dealers 400 in Brooklyn, Mich.Andretti, a 
NASCAR rookie making his first start for Richard Petty's team, just missed 
catching Bodine with a lap time of 39.770-seconds and speed of 181.041 m.p.h. 
near the end of time trials. 
</P>
<P>
 Interim UNLV President Kenny Guinn says he expects more discussions with 
Rollie Massimino regarding a controversial salary package after the Rebel 
basketball coach returns to Las Vegas this weekend. 
</P>
