<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST WESTERN NEVER TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After reading the article on Dan Gordon and what befell his script for the 
film "Wyatt Earp" ("Leave 'Wyatt Earp' Off His Tombstone," Aug. 5), I am left 
with two conclusions.One, that filmgoers lost out on what would have been an 
excellent or at least fascinating film. Two, that Lawrence Kasdan's overhaul of 
the script, however well-intentioned it may have been, was a fatal error. 
</P>
<P>
 And while we're at it, here's a really radical idea: Get Gordon's script and 
make the film as he envisioned it. We're seriously overdue for a good Western. 
</P>
<P>
 JONATHAN YUNGKANS 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
