<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; TRAFFIC COMMISSION POSITIONS OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking applicants for two positions on the Traffic Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 William Bivens and Joseph Greco recently notified the city that they must 
resign from the commission. 
</P>
<P>
 Bivens, a commissioner for more than a year, said he is resigning because his 
job now requires more travel.  
</P>
<P>
 Greco, on the commission since January, resigned because he has moved to 
Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission makes recommendations to the City Council regarding improvement 
of traffic conditions, enforcement of traffic regulations and parking. 
</P>
<P>
 It meets the third Wednesday of each month at 7 p.m. in the Council Chambers, 
25201 Paseo de Alicia. 
</P>
<P>
 The two terms to be filled will expire in January, 1997. The deadline for 
applications is 5 p.m. Sept. 8. LYNN FRANEY 
