<P>
 Applications are being accepted for an open position on the Irvine Residents 
With Disabilities Advisory Board. 
</P>
<P>
 The purpose of the 12-member board is to protect the rights of disabled people 
to take part in community life. Issues addressed by the board include access, 
affordable housing, child and respite care, recreational opportunities and 
transportation. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members serve two-year terms and must be Irvine residents. The 
application deadline is 5 p.m. Sept. 9. For more information, call (714) 
724-6732.RUSS LOAR 
