ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 17TH ST. CLOSURE SET TO DEMOLISH BRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Portions of 17th Street in Santa Ana will be closed starting at midnight 
tonight so that work crews can demolish a bridge that spans the Santa Ana 
Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 The closure will extend from Penn Way to Santiago Avenue and will continue 
through Monday at 5 a.m. The road will be shut down again from midnight Aug. 27 
to 5 a.m. Aug. 29. 
</P>
<P>
 The on-ramps from 17th Street to the Santa Ana Freeway will remain open, but 
the off-ramps from the freeway will be closed. Pedestrians will be prohibited 
from traveling on 17th Street during the closures. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents and merchants will probably hear some noise from the construction 
site, which will be illuminated by floodlights, according to a Caltrans news 
release.  
</P>
<P>
 Some vibrations from the work might also be felt, the statement said. 
</P>
<P>
 Seventeenth Street is a major route between Santa Ana and Tustin. The 
California Department of Transportation asks motorists to follow posted detour 
signs during construction. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
