<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; FIREFIGHTERS TO COLLECT TELETHON DONATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firefighters will collect donations for Jerry Lewis' Labor Day telethon 
Saturday from 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. at Harbor Boulevard and Katella Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is called "Fill the Boot" because firefighters will be asking 
motorists to drop donations into a firefighter's boot. Firefighters nationwide 
will be conducting similar campaigns this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fire Department expects to raise about $20,000 to contribute to the fight 
against muscular dystrophy, firefighter Bob Moore said. The Anaheim Fire 
Department has led all fire agencies in California in collecting for the 
telethon for the past 13 years. 
</P>
<P>
 What's the secret of their success? 
</P>
<P>
 "We have a good attitude," Moore said. "But it's also a good street corner." 
MARTIN MILLER 
