<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVICES ARE SCHEDULED FOR SLAIN UC IRVINE STUDENT ROBERT SAPINOSO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Viewing will be today and Sunday for Robert Sapinoso, the 19-year-old UC 
Irvine student who was shot to death Wednesday as he tried to jot down the 
license number of a van he suspected was involved in a crime. 
</P>
<P>
 Sapinoso, who lived in Westminster, suffered multiple gunshot wounds to his 
upper torso.The killers remain at large. Police said they were driving a 
Toyota-type minivan, possibly oxidized silver. 
</P>
<P>
 The viewing is from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. in the main building at at Forest Lawn, 
4411 Lincoln Ave., Cypress. There will be a vigil at the Church of Our Fathers 
at Forest Lawn Sunday evening at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Funeral Mass will be at 10 a.m. Monday at the Blessed Sacrament Catholic 
Church, 14072 Olive St., Westminster, with burial to follow at Forest Lawn in 
Cypress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082094-0139 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 071577 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
