<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARTELS JOINS HIS SON WITH A FAIR VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coming into Friday night's 20-lap street stock main event at Ventura Raceway, 
Bill Bartels of Los Angeles figured it was his turn to win a feature race 
during the Ventura County Fair, since his son, Ron Bartels of Hawthorne, did it 
last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Bartels figured right, taking the lead on the third lap and coasting to his 
third victory. 
</P>
<P>
 By the sixth lap, Bartels had a one-third of a lap lead over eventual 
second-place finisher James Weston of Santa Barbara, a margin he maintained 
until Jeff Holmes spun on the 10th lap to bring out the caution flag. 
</P>
<P>
 After the restart, Bartels needed four laps to open a quarter-lap lead over 
Weston, which he maintained until the final lap, when he ran into traffic and 
coasted to the finish. 
</P>
