<P>
 FTC Approves Federated-Macy Merger: The U.S. Federal Trade Commission ended 
its review of the proposed merger of Federated Department Stores and R.H. Macy 
& Co., concluding that the planned deal should not be stopped on antitrust 
grounds.New York-based Macy -- operator of the Macy's, Bullock's and I. Magnin 
chains -- and Federated reached a tentative merger agreement July 13. Macy and 
Cincinnati-based Federated -- operator of Bloomingdale's -- compete in some 
common markets such as Georgia, Florida and New York. The state attorney 
general in New York is still reviewing the merger plan for possible antitrust 
implications and has not announced a decision. 
