<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Hebert, who was to be one of Crespi High's best pitchers, has 
transferred to Taft. Hebert, a 6-foot-1 junior right-hander, was 4-1 with a 
1.71 earned-run average during the American Legion regular season for Encino. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Phil White has been selected as head coach at Wenatchee Valley Community 
College in Washington. White, a member of Rio Mesa's CIF championship teams in 
1985 and 1986, will be reviving a baseball program that has been dormant since 
1977. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think that is one of the most exciting things about the job," he said. "The 
first year might be an uphill battle but in the long run it cold be very 
rewarding." 
</P>
<P>
 White, 26, was an assistant at the University of Portland last season. 
Basketball 
</P>
