<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECRUITS FOR ARTS PROGRAM SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ARTS Inc., a nonprofit organization that supplies technical assistance to the 
arts community, is recruiting business, government and community volunteers for 
its Arts Leadership Initiative, a training program created to identify and 
train a new generation of arts leaders. 
</P>
<P>
 About 20-25 people will be selected for the 12-week spring program, which 
starts Sept. 20 and consists of weekend and evening site visits, seminars, 
interviews, panel discussions and performances dealing with current issues 
facing the arts. Cultural democracy, fund raising, financial planning and 
marketing will be covered. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are due by Sept. 2; the program has a $395 registration fee. 
Information: (213) 627-9276. 
</P>
