<HEADLINE>
<P>
'STREISAND: THE CONCERT' ARRIVES ON HBO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you couldn't afford or get tickets to "Barbra Streisand: The Concert," tune 
in to the two-hour HBO special Sunday night as the singer-actress, backed by a 
64-piece orchestra conducted by Marvin Hamlisch, performs her signature songs, 
beginning at 9. 
</P>
<P>
 Many of the public affairs shows will focus on the Cuban refugee crisis, the 
stalled crime bill and the continuing debates over health-care reform. N.F. 
MENDOZA 
</P>
</TEXT>
