<TEXT>
<P>
 The body of a 27-year-old North Hollywood man was found early Friday washed up 
on shore at Lake Piru, a coroner's spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jesus Danilo Carranza drowned Sunday while on an outing with his family. 
Carranza was wearing a life vest but began to struggle in the water, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Family members aboard a rented boat threw him more life vests, but he 
continued to sink. A man aboard the boat dived into the lake to try to save 
Carranza but was unsuccessful, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
