</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON GRANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura city worker struck by a car last week died Friday of head injuries, 
authorities said.  
</P>
<P>
 Ruben Ramirez, 57, of Oxnard was hit by a car as he was retrieving orange 
traffic cones on Victoria Avenue just north of Olivas Park Drive last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 California Highway Patrol officials said the investigation into the incident 
is continuing and no charges have been brought against 28-year-old Patrick J. 
Biando of Ventura, who hit Ramirez as he drove to work in Oxnard, authorities 
said last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Biando was changing lanes and apparently did not see Ramirez until it was too 
late, the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nazir Lalani, Ramirez's boss, said Ramirez had received safety training and 
was wearing an orange traffic vest.  
</P>
<P>
 Ventura city officials with whom Ramirez worked while in the engineering 
division of the Community Services Department expressed sorrow Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a tragic accident . . . that took his life," said Carol Green, 
assistant to the city manager of Ventura. "We haven't experienced anything like 
this before. It's a very distressing event." JASON GRANT 
